<div id="review_21343284" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/21343284" />
    <a title="Melvina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1130119-melvina"><img alt="Melvina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1414317123p2/1130119.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/21343284?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melvina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melvina" href="/user/show/1130119-melvina">Melvina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer21343284" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14268543986315762850">One of my most favorite books and authors of all time. I can&apos;t get enough of Frank&apos;s stories. I also listened to him tell it on an audio recording, and it&apos;s even more awesome listening to his Irish accent. The most compelling characteristic of his writing is the ability to write about a subject as dire and despairing as poverty and neglect, and make it so blisteringly funny, I&apos;m in tears. Then in another chapter, I&apos;m crying with grief over the loss of his siblings and the humiliations of his mot</span>
  <span id="freeText14268543986315762850" style="display:none">One of my most favorite books and authors of all time. I can't get enough of Frank's stories. I also listened to him tell it on an audio recording, and it's even more awesome listening to his Irish accent. The most compelling characteristic of his writing is the ability to write about a subject as dire and despairing as poverty and neglect, and make it so blisteringly funny, I'm in tears. Then in another chapter, I'm crying with grief over the loss of his siblings and the humiliations of his mother. But as awful as his childhood was, he tells it in such a way - GOD, it's funny. I will re-read this many times. It's that good.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14268543986315762850" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


